## Creating an RDS Instance

```bash
# Create a DB subnet group (RDS must span at least 2 AZs)
aws rds create-db-subnet-group \
  --db-subnet-group-name prod-db-subnets \
  --db-subnet-group-description "Production DB subnets" \
  --subnet-ids subnet-private-a subnet-private-b

# Create a security group for RDS
aws ec2 create-security-group \
  --group-name rds-sg \
  --description "RDS access" \
  --vpc-id vpc-xxxxxxxx

# Allow access only from app security group
aws ec2 authorize-security-group-ingress \
  --group-id sg-rds-id \
  --protocol tcp \
  --port 5432 \
  --source-group sg-app-id

# Create the RDS instance
aws rds create-db-instance \
  --db-instance-identifier prod-postgres \
  --db-instance-class db.t3.medium \
  --engine postgres \
  --engine-version 15.4 \
  --master-username dbadmin \
  --master-user-password "UseSecretsManagerInstead" \
  --allocated-storage 100 \
  --storage-type gp3 \
  --db-subnet-group-name prod-db-subnets \
  --vpc-security-group-ids sg-rds-id \
  --multi-az \
  --backup-retention-period 7 \
  --deletion-protection \
  --no-publicly-accessible \
  --storage-encrypted

# Check status
aws rds describe-db-instances \
  --db-instance-identifier prod-postgres \
  --query 'DBInstances[0].[DBInstanceStatus,Endpoint.Address]' \
  --output table
```

---

## Key Parameters Explained

**`--multi-az`** — Creates a standby replica in a different AZ. If the primary fails, AWS automatically fails over to the standby (typically ~60 seconds). Always use in production.

**`--no-publicly-accessible`** — RDS is in private subnets and not reachable from the internet. Always set this.

**`--storage-encrypted`** — Encrypts the EBS volume at rest using KMS. Always set this.

**`--deletion-protection`** — Prevents accidental deletion. Always set in production.

**`--backup-retention-period`** — How many days to keep automated backups. 7–35 days. 0 disables backups (dev only).

