## Connecting to RDS

RDS is in private subnets with no public access. To connect for admin work:

```bash
# Option 1: From an EC2 instance in the same VPC
psql -h prod-postgres.xxxxxxxx.ap-south-1.rds.amazonaws.com \
     -U dbadmin -d myapp

# Option 2: Port forward via SSM (most secure)
aws ssm start-session \
  --target i-ec2-instance-id \
  --document-name AWS-StartPortForwardingSession \
  --parameters '{"portNumber":["5432"],"localPortNumber":["5432"],"host":["prod-postgres.xxxxxxxx.rds.amazonaws.com"]}'

# Then connect locally
psql -h localhost -U dbadmin -d myapp
```

