## Backups and Snapshots

```bash
# Manual snapshot (useful before schema changes)
aws rds create-db-snapshot \
  --db-instance-identifier prod-postgres \
  --db-snapshot-identifier before-migration-2024-06-01

# List snapshots
aws rds describe-db-snapshots \
  --db-instance-identifier prod-postgres \
  --query 'DBSnapshots[*].[DBSnapshotIdentifier,SnapshotCreateTime,Status]' \
  --output table

# Restore from snapshot (creates a NEW instance — does not overwrite existing)
aws rds restore-db-instance-from-db-snapshot \
  --db-instance-identifier restored-postgres \
  --db-snapshot-identifier before-migration-2024-06-01

# Point-in-time restore (restore to any second within retention window)
aws rds restore-db-instance-to-point-in-time \
  --source-db-instance-identifier prod-postgres \
  --target-db-instance-identifier prod-postgres-restored \
  --restore-time 2024-06-01T10:30:00Z
```

